  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">English as a Foreign Language Programme: developing English and methodological skills for teachers to support better English language skills in Brazil</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to provide an integrated approach to English as a Foreign Language (EFL) teacher training programme in public schools in 5 Brazilian State Governments (S&#xE3;o Paulo, Minas Gerais, Mato Grosso, Para&#xED;ba and Tocantis). This project will not only enhance the English proficiency of the public school teachers involved but also leverage the UK&apos;s global expertise in education to demonstrate that investment in EFL is an essential public policy for the country&apos;s development.</narrative>
  </description>
